Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Trim the stem end of the @broccoli{1} and pull off any leaves. Cut 1-2cm thick
'steaks' (1 per person) by slicing from the stem base to the top. Cut the
remaining broccoli into florets.

Place the broccoli steaks and florets on a #baking tray{}. Sprinkle over the
@chermoula spice mix{1}, drizzle with oil and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Toss to coat.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and tender,
~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.
> TIP: The broccoli is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through the
> thickest part of the stem.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125} and pop them onto a piece of
#foil{} with a drizzle of oil, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Pop onto a baking
tray and roast on the bottom shelf of your oven until softened,
~{15-18%minutes}.

While everything roasts, put the @couscous{110%g} in a #bowl{}.

Pour in the @boiled water{220%ml} for the couscous, stir in the
@vegetable stock paste{10%g}, then cover tightly with #cling film{}.

Leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pick the @mint{1}(leaves only) (discard the stalks) and roughly
chop, then peel the @garlic clove{1/2}.

If you don't have a #food processor{}, finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}
and mint, then grate the garlic. Add them to a #medium bowl{} with the
@olive oil{2%tbsp} for the salsa and @red wine vinegar{12%ml}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} and mix well.

If you have a food processor, whizz all the same ingredients together to make
your salsa verde.

When the couscous is ready, fluff it up with a #fork{} and stir through the
@harissa paste{50%g}.

> Use less harissa paste if you'd prefer things milder.

Share your harissa couscous between your bowls, then top with the broccoli
steaks, florets and roasted tomatoes.

Finish by spooning over the salsa verde and crumbling the
@Greek style salad cheese{100%g} over the top.

Enjoy!